The paper deals with the problem of maximizing submodular functions, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and optimization. The paper also introduces new concepts such as submodularity in every orthant and r-wise monotonicity, which are relevant to several areas of computer science such as machine learning, data mining, and game theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
